articles.author: Lim Hui Jie
articles.title: Australia's economy expands 2.3% in the first quarter, slowest growth in 1½ years - CNBC
articles.description: Early Wednesday morning, Reserve Bank of Australia Governor Philip Lowe delivered a speech at the Morgan Stanley Australia Summit, reiterating his position that the central bank will seek to navigate a "narrow path."
articles.content:
View of the Yarra River flowing through Melbourne city centre in Australia.
Australia's first-quarter gross domestic product expanded by 2.3% year-on-year, just slightly below analyst expectations.… [+2669 chars]
